					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">NSA (or 8name, a clone that works better on Windows 2000 and Windows XP) is for title screens and for playfields in non-scrolling games such as Duck Hunt or Tetris. Most developers of NES scrolling games made their own map editors depending on the structure of their game engine. For example, the developers of Super Mario Bros. used <em>something like</em> Mario Improvement to make levels.</div>

